WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:04.871
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

00:04.871 --> 00:07.173
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

00:07.173 --> 00:09.109
MY JOB
IS TO BE RIGHT HERE

00:09.109 --> 00:11.144
SO YOU CAN TALK TO ME
ABOUT ANYTHING.

00:11.144 --> 00:12.412
HOW DO YOU KNOW
SO MUCH ABOUT THIS?

00:12.412 --> 00:13.880
I WAS AN ADDICT.

00:13.880 --> 00:17.518
I JUST NEED YOU TO KNOW
HOW REALLY PISSED OFF I AM.

00:17.518 --> 00:18.985
YEAH, BUT WHAT ROOM
ARE YOU IN?

00:18.985 --> 00:20.821
WHY DO YOU KEEP ASKING ME
ALL THESE QUESTIONS?

00:20.821 --> 00:22.756
I JUST WANT TO KNOW.
IT CHANGES EVERY DAY.

00:22.756 --> 00:24.424
I DON'T WANT TO DO THIS.
I DON'T WANT TO DO THIS.

00:24.424 --> 00:27.027
WELL, WHY NOW?
ALL RIGHT, MAN. SERIOUSLY.

00:28.261 --> 00:31.431
WHAT THE HELL?

00:31.431 --> 00:33.767
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

00:33.767 --> 00:36.269
♪♪♪♪

00:36.269 --> 00:39.339
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

00:39.339 --> 00:40.874
[ SIGHS ]
OH, JESUS.

00:40.874 --> 00:43.844
ALL RIGHT, LANDON.
UM, JUST ‐‐ JUST GO.

00:43.844 --> 00:46.346
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
NOT A CHANCE.

00:46.346 --> 00:48.849
WHO IS THIS?
ALL RIGHT, STOP, STOP, STOP.

00:48.849 --> 00:49.783
STOP.
WAIT, I'VE SEEN YOU BEFORE.

00:49.783 --> 00:51.217
STOP. GO.
YOU NEED TO LEAVE.

00:51.217 --> 00:53.654
OH, YOU'RE THAT COP THAT WAS
IN THE LOBBY OF THE SARANDON?

00:53.654 --> 00:55.121
‐OKAY. ALL RIGHT. JUST GO.
‐I THOUGHT HE WAS STRAIGHT.

00:55.121 --> 00:56.456
I TOLD YOU HE WAS STRAIGHT,
BUT HE'S NOT.

00:56.456 --> 00:57.924
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO. GO.
I WAS WRONG.

00:57.924 --> 00:59.159
COME ON. ALL RIGHT.
I WAS WRONG ABOUT HIM.

00:59.159 --> 01:01.167
MAYBE I'M WRONG
ABOUT WYATT TOO.

01:01.167 --> 01:02.235
ALL RIGHT, NO, NO, NO.
COME ON.

01:02.235 --> 01:03.403
COME ON. STOP THIS.
NO, TRUST ME.

01:03.403 --> 01:06.072
STOP THIS. YOU'RE DRUNK.
JUST RELAX, OKAY?

01:06.072 --> 01:07.307
RELAX.

01:07.307 --> 01:08.975
HI, I'M LANDON.

01:08.975 --> 01:09.809
JEFFERY.

01:09.809 --> 01:11.244
ALL RIGHT,
AND YOU ARE?

01:11.244 --> 01:12.813
[ SCOFFS ]
JEFFERY!

01:12.813 --> 01:14.014
ALL RIGHT.

01:14.014 --> 01:15.649
HE'S A FRIEND, OKAY, SO...

01:15.649 --> 01:17.183
OH, OH, OH.
NOW CAN YOU JUST GO?

01:17.183 --> 01:18.218
NO WAY.
NO, NO.

01:18.218 --> 01:19.152
FRIEND, HUH?
LEAVE.

01:19.152 --> 01:20.220
YES, A FRIEND.
STOP. COME ON.

01:20.220 --> 01:21.221
WELL, IT LOOKS TO ME
LIKE YOU AND THIS FRIEND

01:21.221 --> 01:23.089
ARE DOING MORE
THAN ANYONE KNOWS.

01:23.089 --> 01:24.124
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
YOU HAD A FRIEND.

01:24.124 --> 01:25.325
NO, I DIDN'T.
NOW...

01:25.325 --> 01:27.227
MY, MY, JEFFERY,
YOU HAVE GRADUATED.

01:27.227 --> 01:28.895
ARE YOU INTO
THREESOMES, DADDY?

01:28.895 --> 01:31.031
‐LANDON, COME ON. LEAVE.
‐WHAT? NO, I'M NOT GOING.

01:31.031 --> 01:32.298
YOU'VE GOT ME UP HERE
AND EXCITED,

01:32.298 --> 01:33.399
AND I'M GONNA
GET SOME.

01:33.399 --> 01:34.768
TRUST ME,
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE IT, OKAY?

01:34.768 --> 01:36.002
WHEN THERE'S MORE
THAN TWO GUYS,

01:36.002 --> 01:37.003
EVERY PART OF YOUR BODY
IS STIMULATED.

01:37.003 --> 01:38.071
‐LANDON.
‐IT'S AMAZING.

01:38.071 --> 01:40.641
JUST RELAX, OKAY? TRUST ME.
GO. GO.

01:40.641 --> 01:41.775
OH, NO, I'M NOT GOING.
I'M NOT GONNA ‐‐

01:41.775 --> 01:43.276
YOU GOT ME UP HERE,
AND I'M EXCITED,

01:43.276 --> 01:45.011
AND THIS IS GOING DOWN,
OKAY?

01:45.011 --> 01:46.012
I THINK THE THREE OF US
ARE ABOUT ‐‐

01:46.012 --> 01:47.781
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING
AT ME LIKE THAT FOR?

01:47.781 --> 01:49.883
I'M PRETTY HOT, TOO,
YOU KNOW?

01:49.883 --> 01:50.851
CAN YOU GO?

01:50.851 --> 01:52.018
NO, I'M NOT
GOING ANYWHERE, OKAY?

01:52.018 --> 01:53.119
THIS IS GONNA BE FUN.

01:53.119 --> 01:54.755
WE'RE JUST GONNA DO
WHAT WE ALWAYS DO.

01:54.755 --> 01:56.890
WHAT?! WE DON'T ALWAYS
DO <i>ANYTHING.</i>

01:56.890 --> 01:58.158
WELL,
WE DID ONE TIME BEFORE.

01:58.158 --> 01:59.492
TRUST ME.
NO.

01:59.492 --> 02:01.367
I DIDN'T INVITE YOU UP HERE
FOR SEX, LANDON,

02:01.367 --> 02:02.769
SO JUST GET OUT.
NO, BUT YOU DIDN'T STOP ME.

02:02.769 --> 02:06.039
OOH, DAMN, JEFFERY.
LANDON.

02:06.039 --> 02:08.474
THAT IS NICE.
WOULD YOU STOP THAT?

02:08.474 --> 02:10.944
I DON'T NEED TO KNOW
YOUR NAME ‐‐ I DON'T ‐‐

02:10.944 --> 02:12.278
BUT BEFORE
THE END OF TONIGHT,

02:12.278 --> 02:13.847
YOU'RE GONNA KNOW MINE.
IT'S LANDON.

02:13.847 --> 02:14.715
Jeffery: OKAY, HEY!

02:14.715 --> 02:16.116
SAY IT. SAY IT.
OH, MY GOD.

02:18.051 --> 02:19.686
ALL RIGHT. HEY! HEY!
ALL RIGHT. STOP IT.

02:19.686 --> 02:21.688
LANDON, STOP IT.
JUSTIN!

02:21.688 --> 02:23.156
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
STOP IT. STOP IT.

02:23.156 --> 02:24.558
STOP ‐‐ STOP IT. STOP IT.
WAIT ONE SECOND.

02:24.558 --> 02:26.660
LET GO!

02:26.660 --> 02:28.895
GET OUT OF HERE. GET OUT!
THE HELL?

02:28.895 --> 02:31.064
JUST GO!
I'M NOT INTO THE CHOKING.

02:31.064 --> 02:32.699
ALL RIGHT. GOOD. GO.

02:32.699 --> 02:34.735
YOU'RE DAMN STRAIGHT
I'M GONNA GO.

02:34.735 --> 02:36.236
MY JACKET.

02:36.236 --> 02:37.604
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU PEOPLE?

02:37.604 --> 02:38.939
GET OUT!

02:38.939 --> 02:41.307
YEAH, THIS? WEIRD.
GOOD. GO.

02:41.307 --> 02:42.208
I'LL SEE YOU LATER,
JEFFERY.

02:42.208 --> 02:43.844
NO, YOU WON'T.
GET OUT OF HERE.

02:43.844 --> 02:45.345
WEIRD.

02:45.345 --> 02:55.021
♪♪♪♪

03:01.535 --> 03:02.636
GET OUT!
WHO WAS THAT?

03:02.636 --> 03:04.037
I SAID, "GET OUT!"
JEFFERY? WHO WAS IT?

03:04.037 --> 03:05.238
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING IN HERE?

03:05.238 --> 03:07.140
I CAME HERE TO SEE YOU!

03:07.140 --> 03:08.374
UNINVITED.

03:08.374 --> 03:10.343
YOU KNOW
I CAN'T CALL YOU.

03:10.343 --> 03:11.845
NO. YOU CAN'T.

03:11.845 --> 03:14.515
YEAH, RIGHT, 'CAUSE YOUR MOM
IS WATCHING MY EVERY MOVE.

03:14.515 --> 03:16.016
JUST GET OUT OF HERE.

03:16.016 --> 03:18.919
NO! NOT UNTIL YOU TELL ME
WHO THAT WAS.

03:18.919 --> 03:20.721
NONE OF YOUR
DAMN BUSINESS.

03:20.721 --> 03:22.623
JEFFERY.
NO. I DON'T OWE YOU ANYTHING.

03:22.623 --> 03:24.357
I'M NOT GONNA ANSWER
ANY OF YOUR QUESTIONS.

03:24.357 --> 03:25.726
WHY DON'T YOU JUST GO HOME
TO YOUR WIFE?

03:25.726 --> 03:26.693
GO.

03:26.693 --> 03:28.494
I WANT TO SEE YOU.

03:28.494 --> 03:29.763
JUSTIN,
I'M NOT DOING THIS.

03:29.763 --> 03:31.598
YOU CAN'T DO THIS TO ME.

03:31.598 --> 03:33.433
<i>YOU</i> ARE DOING IT TO <i>YOU.</i>

03:33.433 --> 03:34.668
JEFFERY.

03:34.668 --> 03:36.469
WHAT?

03:36.469 --> 03:37.638
I FELL FOR YOU,

03:37.638 --> 03:39.906
AND YOU BRING THAT
SON OF A BITCH IN HERE?!

03:39.906 --> 03:41.074
JUSTIN...
[ STAMMERS ]

03:41.074 --> 03:42.643
I'M IN LOVE WITH YOU.

03:42.643 --> 03:43.577
WHAT?

03:43.577 --> 03:46.112
YOU HEARD ME.

03:46.112 --> 03:48.081
JUSTIN, YOU JUST MET ME.
I KNOW.

03:48.081 --> 03:50.250
I KNOW IT SOUNDS CRAZY,

03:50.250 --> 03:53.353
BUT I THINK ABOUT YOU
ALL DAY AND ALL NIGHT.

03:53.353 --> 03:55.055
OH, MY GOD.
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

03:55.055 --> 03:57.123
AND YOU COME IN HERE
WITH THAT GUY?

03:57.123 --> 03:59.560
I DON'T BELONG TO YOU!

03:59.560 --> 04:01.001
WHO IS HE?
GET OUT.

04:01.001 --> 04:02.803
WHO IS HE?!

04:02.803 --> 04:04.137
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

04:04.137 --> 04:07.040
HUH? ARE YOU GONNA
ATTACK ME AGAIN?

04:07.040 --> 04:08.308
HMM?

04:08.308 --> 04:09.342
NO.

04:11.945 --> 04:14.881
NO, I'M NOT GOING
TO ATTACK YOU AGAIN.

04:14.881 --> 04:16.750
YOU SURE? 'CAUSE YOU HAD
THAT LOOK IN YOUR EYES.

04:16.750 --> 04:18.952
I'M NOT GOING
TO ATTACK YOU, OKAY?

04:22.155 --> 04:23.857
THEN LEAVE.

04:27.994 --> 04:30.363
PLEASE,
DON'T MAKE ME LEAVE.

04:32.065 --> 04:34.000
YOU NEED HELP.

04:34.000 --> 04:35.034
I KNOW THAT.

04:35.034 --> 04:36.870
GET THERAPY.

04:36.870 --> 04:38.772
YOU'RE A THERAPIST.
WHY DON'T YOU HELP ME?

04:38.772 --> 04:41.441
NO. NO. NO.
NOT LIKE THIS.

04:41.441 --> 04:42.408
JEFFERY...

04:42.408 --> 04:43.544
GO.

04:48.481 --> 04:51.217
[ SIGHS ]

04:51.217 --> 04:54.921
WHAT HAVE YOU DONE
TO ME?

04:54.921 --> 04:57.123
JUSTIN,
WH‐WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

04:57.123 --> 04:59.325
I WASN'T LIKE THIS
UNTIL YOU.

05:01.735 --> 05:04.437
NO. YOU WERE IN THE BACK
OF YOUR PATROL CAR,

05:04.437 --> 05:05.872
SUCKING OFF PRISONERS.

05:05.872 --> 05:07.908
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

05:07.908 --> 05:09.442
YOU GONNA HIT ME AGAIN?

05:09.442 --> 05:12.779
DON'T SAY THAT ABOUT ME.

05:12.779 --> 05:14.014
GET OFF OF ME.

05:18.284 --> 05:20.253
IT'S TRUE.

05:20.253 --> 05:21.922
NO. NO.

05:21.922 --> 05:23.389
YOU DID SOMETHING TO ME.

05:23.389 --> 05:24.725
I DID NOTHING TO YOU.

05:24.725 --> 05:25.792
NO, I HAVE ‐‐

05:25.792 --> 05:29.295
I HAVE NEVER ENJOYED THIS
UNTIL YOU.

05:29.295 --> 05:30.664
[ SIGHS ]

05:33.867 --> 05:35.068
JUSTIN...

05:35.068 --> 05:36.970
YOU HAVE ALWAYS
ENJOYED IT.

05:36.970 --> 05:40.006
♪♪♪♪

05:42.776 --> 05:44.911
YOU'RE JUST NEVER WERE
GONNA ADMIT IT UNTIL NOW.

05:47.213 --> 05:49.883
JEFFERY, PLEASE.

05:49.883 --> 05:52.886
JUSTIN, PLEASE LEAVE.

05:52.886 --> 05:55.889
♪♪♪♪

05:55.889 --> 05:58.291
I LOVE YOU.

05:58.291 --> 06:00.026
YOU DON'T KNOW ME.

06:00.026 --> 06:02.202
I DON'T KNOW ANY OF THIS.

06:02.202 --> 06:04.705
BUT I DO KNOW
THAT I LOVE YOU.

06:10.110 --> 06:12.078
WELL...[SIGHS]
ALL THE MORE REASON

06:12.078 --> 06:14.014
FOR YOU TO GET HELP.

06:15.415 --> 06:16.617
NO. I'M NOT LEAVING.

06:16.617 --> 06:17.784
OKAY.

06:17.784 --> 06:19.219
THEN I'LL LEAVE.
NO. NO. NO. NO.

06:19.219 --> 06:20.921
HEY. HEY! JUSTIN...
NO, JEFFERY. JEFFERY, NO.

06:20.921 --> 06:22.723
LET ME GO. LET ME GO.

06:22.723 --> 06:25.191
WHERE ARE YOU GONNA GO?
YOU GONNA GO TO HIM?

06:25.191 --> 06:26.660
LET ME GO.

06:26.660 --> 06:28.662
AND WHAT IF I AM?

06:28.662 --> 06:30.764
DON'T SAY THAT.

06:30.764 --> 06:32.432
WHAT IF I AM?

06:32.432 --> 06:34.935
OH, I SEE
WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO DO.

06:34.935 --> 06:36.570
WHAT AM I TRYING TO DO?

06:36.570 --> 06:37.704
YOU WANT ME TO ATTACK YOU

06:37.704 --> 06:40.006
SO THAT YOU HAVE
A REASON TO LEAVE.

06:41.575 --> 06:44.778
OH...NO.

06:44.778 --> 06:46.479
IS THAT WHAT
YOU THINK I'M DOING?

06:46.479 --> 06:47.548
IS IT?

06:50.717 --> 06:54.054
I NEED YOU TO MOVE.

06:54.054 --> 06:55.856
FINE, GO.

06:55.856 --> 06:57.524
♪♪♪♪

06:57.524 --> 06:58.725
YEAH. GO TO HIM.

07:02.302 --> 07:04.871
♪♪♪♪

07:04.871 --> 07:07.340
MOM. MOM. LADY, HEY. LADY, STOP.

07:07.340 --> 07:08.642
STOP!
MOM, STOP IT.

07:08.642 --> 07:10.143
MOM, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

07:10.143 --> 07:13.179
♪♪♪♪

07:18.752 --> 07:20.253
MOM ‐‐ MOM!
WOULD YOU STOP IT?

07:20.253 --> 07:21.755
STOP! MOM!

07:21.755 --> 07:24.791
♪♪♪♪

07:27.393 --> 07:28.762
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

07:35.368 --> 07:37.070
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

07:40.440 --> 07:43.476
♪♪♪♪

07:49.282 --> 07:52.318
♪♪♪♪

08:10.877 --> 08:13.780
♪♪♪♪

08:17.217 --> 08:19.720
SIT DOWN.

08:19.720 --> 08:21.688
HI.
TALK TO ME.

08:21.688 --> 08:23.890
WELL, I HAVE A NUMBER.

08:25.491 --> 08:26.593
WHAT, AND THAT'S IT?

08:26.593 --> 08:28.061
WELL, HIS NUMBER CHANGED.

08:28.061 --> 08:30.063
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT ABOUT HIS OLD NUMBERS?

08:30.063 --> 08:31.231
WELL, IT CHANGED, AS WELL,
ACCORDING

08:31.231 --> 08:34.100
TO THE CELL‐PHONE‐TOWER
DATA LOG.

08:34.100 --> 08:36.402
OKAY, LET ME TALK TO HIM.
GIVE ME A PHONE.

08:36.402 --> 08:38.104
YOU'RE GOING TO SPOOK HIM.
GIVE ME A PHONE.

08:38.104 --> 08:39.439
I NEED TO TALK TO HIM.

08:39.439 --> 08:40.541
HEY, LISTEN.

08:40.541 --> 08:42.075
I NEED HIM ON THE PHONE
FOR 12 MINUTES

08:42.075 --> 08:43.376
IN ORDER
TO PINPOINT HIS LOCATION.

08:43.376 --> 08:44.945
YEAH. YEAH.
LET ME TALK TO HIM.

08:44.945 --> 08:46.079
WHAT'S THE NUMBER?

08:46.079 --> 08:47.380
IF YOU SPOOK HIM,
WE'RE GONNA LOSE HIM.

08:47.380 --> 08:48.314
I UNDERSTAND THAT.

08:48.314 --> 08:49.950
I'M WILLING TO TAKE
THAT CHANCE.

08:49.950 --> 08:51.417
WHAT IS THE NUMBER?

08:51.417 --> 08:53.019
OKAY.

08:53.019 --> 08:55.255
WELL, I HAVE THREE,

08:55.255 --> 08:57.357
AND IT'S ONE OF THESE.
[ GLASS CLINKS ]

08:57.357 --> 08:59.492
OKAY, FINE.
I'LL CALL ALL THREE.

08:59.492 --> 09:01.502
YOU KNOW HIS VOICE?

09:01.502 --> 09:03.804
YES, I KNOW HIS VOICE.

09:03.804 --> 09:04.638
OKAY.

09:04.638 --> 09:07.674
♪♪♪♪

09:22.388 --> 09:24.157
[ Ringing ]

09:24.157 --> 09:26.727
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

09:26.727 --> 09:27.761
YO.

09:27.761 --> 09:28.829
How are you, baby?

09:28.829 --> 09:30.230
I'M ALL RIGHT.

09:30.230 --> 09:32.566
IS IT STILL HOT
OUT THERE?

09:32.566 --> 09:35.135
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
YEAH, BUT IT'S COOLING OFF.

09:35.135 --> 09:36.136
Okay.

09:36.136 --> 09:38.071
WELL, YOU KNOW
SHE'S HERE?

09:38.071 --> 09:39.405
WHERE?

09:39.405 --> 09:42.308
I don't know which room exactly,
but she's here.

09:42.308 --> 09:43.376
SHE CAN'T GO TOO FAR.

09:43.376 --> 09:44.878
THEY LOOKING FOR HER ASS
EVERYWHERE.

09:44.878 --> 09:46.647
YEAH. I KNOW.

09:46.647 --> 09:48.515
HEY, MAYBE I SHOULD
TELL THE COPS THAT SHE'S HERE.

09:48.515 --> 09:51.251
NO! NO!

09:51.251 --> 09:54.054
B‐BUT THEN,
SHE WOULD GET GOT?

09:54.054 --> 09:55.488
BUT I WANT THAT BITCH!

09:55.488 --> 09:56.489
Baby...

09:56.489 --> 09:58.158
LOOK ‐‐
YOU KNOW I WANT HER.

09:58.158 --> 09:59.960
YEAH,
AND I KNOW THE WAY YOU HIT.

09:59.960 --> 10:02.503
YEAH, AND THAT...
SHE'S MINE.

10:02.503 --> 10:04.838
WELL, SHE WON'T
TELL ME WHAT ROOM.

10:04.838 --> 10:06.006
WHY?

10:06.006 --> 10:08.108
I DON'T KNOW.

10:08.108 --> 10:09.342
BUT YOU KNOW CANDACE.

10:09.342 --> 10:10.777
SHE...

10:10.777 --> 10:12.946
SHE SENSES THINGS.

10:12.946 --> 10:15.281
DAMN, THAT BITCH IS LIKE
A CAT WITH NINE LIVES.

10:15.281 --> 10:17.818
YEAH, BUT I'M TAKING ALL OF THEM
WHEN I CATCH HER.

10:17.818 --> 10:18.819
[ Call waiting beeps ]

10:18.819 --> 10:20.286
HOLD ON.

10:20.286 --> 10:21.454
YEAH?

10:21.454 --> 10:23.524
WAR?

10:23.524 --> 10:25.291
MAN, WHO'S THIS?

10:25.291 --> 10:27.528
JIM CRYER.

10:27.528 --> 10:28.862
MAN, HOW YOU GET
THIS NUMBER?!

10:28.862 --> 10:30.296
Don't you worry
about that, all right?

10:30.296 --> 10:32.298
I need to see you.
MAN, THAT AIN'T HAPPENING.

10:32.298 --> 10:33.634
YO, HOLD ON.
Don't you hang up ‐‐

10:33.634 --> 10:35.836
[ Beep ]

10:35.836 --> 10:37.170
YO, I NEED
TO CALL YOU BACK.

10:37.170 --> 10:39.239
BABY, WHAT'S UP?

10:39.239 --> 10:41.575
SOMEBODY I NEED TO SHAKE.

10:41.575 --> 10:43.409
OKAY.

10:43.409 --> 10:44.778
I'LL CALL YOU LATER.

10:47.147 --> 10:48.481
ALL RIGHT.

10:48.481 --> 10:50.016
[ BEEP ]
Hello?

10:50.016 --> 10:51.652
WHAT?

10:51.652 --> 10:54.154
I NEED TO MEET YOU.

10:54.154 --> 10:55.556
MAN, I AIN'T MEETING YOU.

10:55.556 --> 10:57.524
WAR, THIS IS SERIOUS.

10:57.524 --> 10:59.259
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

10:59.259 --> 11:01.568
[ SCOFFS ] YEAH.
LOOK WHO'S BEGGING.

11:01.568 --> 11:04.337
Listen. I can help you
get out of this, okay?

11:04.337 --> 11:07.140
OUT OF WHAT?

11:07.140 --> 11:10.243
THE WARRANTS
THAT ARE OUT FOR YOU.

11:10.243 --> 11:12.813
Yeah, and what you want
in return?

11:12.813 --> 11:15.415
LISTEN TO ME. LISTEN TO ME.
WE HAD A DEAL. OKAY?

11:15.415 --> 11:17.651
I KNOW THAT
THERE ARE MORE PICTURES,

11:17.651 --> 11:20.186
SO I WILL TAKE CARE OF YOU,
AND YOU WILL TAKE CARE OF ME.

11:20.186 --> 11:21.421
OKAY?

11:23.757 --> 11:25.826
MAN, I AIN'T
DOING A DAMN THING, BRO.

11:25.826 --> 11:28.261
WAR, WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR CODE?

11:28.261 --> 11:31.364
CODE?
Yes, your code.

11:31.364 --> 11:32.866
MAN, I'M A THUG, BRO.

11:32.866 --> 11:34.868
I know that.
AND YOU A JUDGE.

11:34.868 --> 11:36.202
♪♪♪♪

11:36.202 --> 11:38.872
WAR...

11:38.872 --> 11:40.173
YO, MAN,
I'M HANGING UP THE PHONE.

11:40.173 --> 11:41.407
YOU DON'T NEED TO CALL
THIS NUMBER BACK NO MORE

11:41.407 --> 11:42.242
'CAUSE IT'S GONE.

11:42.242 --> 11:43.610
Warrick, don't you ‐‐
[ BEEP ]

11:43.610 --> 11:45.879
MAN, GET RID
OF THAT PHONE, BRO.

11:45.879 --> 11:47.180
[ SCOFFS ]

11:51.151 --> 11:53.186
DAMN IT!

11:53.186 --> 11:56.156
WELL, I COULDN'T GET A LOCK
ON THE LOCATION.

11:56.156 --> 11:57.624
WHAT DID YOU GET?

11:57.624 --> 11:59.960
JUST A GENERAL AREA.

11:59.960 --> 12:01.301
DAMN IT!

12:01.301 --> 12:02.836
WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH THIS GUY?

12:02.836 --> 12:04.137
[ SIGHS ]

12:04.137 --> 12:06.840
IF I DON'T FIND HIM,
ALL HELL'S GONNA BREAK LOOSE.

12:06.840 --> 12:09.075
I THINK IT ALREADY HAS.

12:09.075 --> 12:10.210
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

12:10.210 --> 12:11.912
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

12:11.912 --> 12:14.548
WELL, HAVEN'T YOU
SEEN THE NEWS?

12:14.548 --> 12:16.416
WHAT NEWS?

12:16.416 --> 12:17.951
LET ME PULL IT UP
FOR YOU.

12:20.821 --> 12:24.224
<i>D.A. JENNIFER SALLISON'S BODY</i>
<i>WAS FOUND HERE,</i>

12:24.224 --> 12:26.292
<i>RIGHT OUTSIDE OF OUR STATION.</i>

12:26.292 --> 12:28.529
<i>THE BODY HAD "CRYER VICTIM"</i>

12:28.529 --> 12:32.298
<i>WRITTEN ON THE PLASTIC WRAP</i>
<i>THAT SHE WAS FOUND IN.</i>

12:32.298 --> 12:34.568
DAMN IT!

12:34.568 --> 12:36.369
WHAT THE HELL?

12:36.369 --> 12:37.437
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?!

12:37.437 --> 12:38.404
YOU DIDN'T KNOW
ABOUT THIS?

12:38.404 --> 12:40.173
NO, I DIDN'T KNOW
ABOUT TH‐‐

12:40.173 --> 12:41.742
[ Whispering ] DOES IT LOOK
LIKE I KNEW ABOUT THIS?

12:41.742 --> 12:43.443
JIM...

12:43.443 --> 12:44.945
IT'S EVERYWHERE.

12:44.945 --> 12:47.881
♪♪♪♪

12:54.555 --> 12:56.022
[ KNOCKS AT DOOR ]

13:01.768 --> 13:03.870
‐HEY.
‐SHH‐SHH, HE'S SLEEPING.

13:03.870 --> 13:05.305
COME IN.

13:05.305 --> 13:07.774
♪♪♪♪

13:07.774 --> 13:09.743
Anna:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

13:09.743 --> 13:11.111
Jeffery:
HOW'S HE DOING?

13:11.111 --> 13:13.046
HE'S FINE.

13:13.046 --> 13:14.314
WHAT'S HE DOING?

13:14.314 --> 13:16.750
OH. HE'S RESTING.

13:19.052 --> 13:20.286
OKAY.

13:20.286 --> 13:21.487
YOU WANT TO SEE HIM?

13:21.487 --> 13:23.890
NO. IT'S FINE.
I DON'T WANT TO WAKE HIM.

13:23.890 --> 13:25.792
I KNOW.
IT'S HARD TO GET HIM TO SLEEP.

13:25.792 --> 13:28.194
SO WHENEVER HE'S DOING IT,
I JUST LET HIM.

13:28.194 --> 13:30.697
YEAH? THAT'S GOOD.

13:30.697 --> 13:33.299
HE'S A NICE GUY.
I LIKE HIM.

13:33.299 --> 13:34.768
IS HE?
YEAH. [ CHUCKLES ]

13:34.768 --> 13:35.769
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT?

13:35.769 --> 13:37.704
WELL, I JUST HAVEN'T
SEEN A NICE GUY

13:37.704 --> 13:40.340
IN A LONG TIME ‐‐
A COUPLE OF YEARS PROBABLY.

13:40.340 --> 13:42.375
I MEAN, THAT'S THE GUY
WHO I FEEL IN LOVE WITH.

13:43.644 --> 13:44.811
"IN LOVE"?

13:44.811 --> 13:47.247
YEAH. I LOVE HIM.
OH. I'M...

13:47.247 --> 13:48.882
I JUST DIDN'T KNOW
YOU TWO WERE...

13:48.882 --> 13:50.617
OH. WELL, NO. WE'RE NOT,

13:50.617 --> 13:51.518
LIKE, YOU KNOW,
I DON'T...

13:51.518 --> 13:53.419
I CAN LOVE HIM
AND NOT BE...

13:53.419 --> 13:55.355
YEAH. YEAH. I‐I KNOW.
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:55.355 --> 13:56.489
'CAUSE HE'S NOT GAY.

13:56.489 --> 13:58.091
I AM.

13:58.091 --> 14:00.160
OKAY. WELL, YOU KNOW
I DON'T CARE EITHER WAY

14:00.160 --> 14:02.335
SO THAT'S...
NO. NO.

14:02.335 --> 14:03.937
YEAH, I KNOW.

14:03.937 --> 14:07.107
ANNE, THANK YOU
FOR DOING THIS.

14:07.107 --> 14:09.175
I'M JUST DOING MY JOB.

14:09.175 --> 14:11.111
WELL, YOU'RE DOING
REALLY GOOD AT IT.

14:11.111 --> 14:13.714
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

14:13.714 --> 14:16.182
SO, I OWE HIS MOTHER
A PHONE CALL

14:16.182 --> 14:17.651
ABOUT HIS PROGRESS,

14:17.651 --> 14:20.153
AND I GUESS I CAN TELL HER
THAT EVERYTHING IS GOING GREAT?

14:20.153 --> 14:22.288
YEAH. YEAH. YOU CAN TELL HER
THAT EVERYTHING IS FINE.

14:22.288 --> 14:23.690
OKAY. AWESOME.

14:23.690 --> 14:25.158
SO I'LL SEE YOU LATER?
SURE.

14:25.158 --> 14:27.327
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]
MY PHONE IS VIBRATING.

14:27.327 --> 14:28.529
OH, OKAY.
YEAH. WELL, TAKE IT.

14:28.529 --> 14:30.463
THANK YOU.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

14:33.333 --> 14:36.069
[ BEEP ]

14:36.069 --> 14:37.103
HELLO?

14:37.103 --> 14:39.205
Oscar: HI.

14:39.205 --> 14:40.140
WHO IS THIS?

14:40.140 --> 14:41.542
This is Oscar.

14:41.542 --> 14:42.475
WHO?

14:42.475 --> 14:43.476
You know,
the guy you talked to

14:43.476 --> 14:44.545
in the parking lot
the other day?

14:44.545 --> 14:46.279
OH, YEAH. YEAH. I...

14:46.279 --> 14:48.715
You haven't called
about my offer.

14:48.715 --> 14:52.018
WELL, I DON'T THINK
I'M GONNA BE ABLE TO HELP.

14:52.018 --> 14:54.588
I will up my offer to you
to $50,000.

14:54.588 --> 14:57.090
I'M SORRY,
BUT I'M NOT FOR SALE.

14:57.090 --> 14:58.759
No. Wait. Wait.
Okay, listen. Listen to me.

14:58.759 --> 15:00.293
NO. THIS IS WRONG,

15:00.293 --> 15:02.402
AND I DON'T WANT TO BE
A PART OF IT.

15:02.402 --> 15:04.738
Well...
Just think about it.

15:04.738 --> 15:07.240
LISTEN. GOODBYE.
AND PLEASE DON'T CALL ME AGAIN.

15:09.109 --> 15:11.444
[ BEEP ]

15:11.444 --> 15:13.647
HE SOUNDS JEALOUS.

15:13.647 --> 15:15.048
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE SLEEPING.

15:15.048 --> 15:17.250
[ SIGHS ]
I SLEEP LIKE A CAT.

15:17.250 --> 15:18.952
OH, I SEE THAT.

15:18.952 --> 15:20.787
IS JEFFERY GONE?

15:20.787 --> 15:22.789
YEAH.

15:22.789 --> 15:24.024
GOOD. GOOD.

15:24.024 --> 15:26.259
WHY?
YOU DON'T WANT TO SEE HIM?

15:26.259 --> 15:27.260
NOT YET.

15:27.260 --> 15:29.329
WHY NOT?

15:29.329 --> 15:31.297
HE'S JUST GOT THIS LOOK
OF WORRY AND SYMPATHY

15:31.297 --> 15:32.232
EVERY TIME HE LOOKS AT ME.

15:32.232 --> 15:35.235
I HATE IT.
WELL, HE DOES WORRY.

15:35.235 --> 15:36.503
YEAH.

15:36.503 --> 15:38.038
IT'S 'CAUSE
HE'S IN LOVE WITH ME.

15:38.038 --> 15:41.374
YEAH, I ‐‐
I HEARD THAT.

15:41.374 --> 15:42.776
BUT YOU KNOW I'M NOT...

15:42.776 --> 15:44.344
I KNOW.

15:44.344 --> 15:45.846
[ CHUCKLES ] YEAH.

15:45.846 --> 15:47.380
SO HE'S WISHFUL THINKING.

15:47.380 --> 15:51.184
I DON'T KNOW IF HE IS.

15:51.184 --> 15:52.586
WHAT? YOU SEE
SOMETHING ELSE?

15:52.586 --> 15:53.820
ACTUALLY, I DO.

15:53.820 --> 15:55.488
I SEE A FRIEND
THAT LOVES YOU,

15:55.488 --> 15:57.157
AND YOU SAID NO ONE
LOVES YOU, RIGHT?

15:57.157 --> 15:59.325
WELL, HE DOES.

15:59.325 --> 16:02.068
YEAH, JUST 'CAUSE HE WANTS
TO HAVE SEX WITH ME.

16:02.068 --> 16:04.004
WELL, [STAMMERS]
I DON'T KNOW IF HE DOES,

16:04.004 --> 16:06.339
BUT WHAT I SEE FROM HIM
IS THAT...

16:06.339 --> 16:08.474
HIS LOVE HAS
NO CONDITIONS.

16:08.474 --> 16:11.778
♪♪♪♪

16:11.778 --> 16:12.713
REALLY?

16:12.713 --> 16:14.748
YEAH.

16:17.951 --> 16:19.052
WELL, THE MAN YOU WERE
TALKING TO ON THE PHONE

16:19.052 --> 16:21.021
HAS CONDITIONS.

16:21.021 --> 16:22.488
EXCUSE ME?

16:22.488 --> 16:24.024
THE MAN ON THE PHONE?

16:24.024 --> 16:25.592
OH. NO.

16:25.592 --> 16:26.392
THAT'S, UM...

16:26.392 --> 16:29.195
THAT'S NO ONE I KNOW.

16:29.195 --> 16:30.531
WHO IS IT?

16:30.531 --> 16:32.999
JUST ‐‐ I DON'T KNOW.
JUST SOME TELEMARKETER THAT...

16:32.999 --> 16:34.535
HE WANTED A FAVOR.

16:34.535 --> 16:37.538
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT HE WANTED.

16:37.538 --> 16:40.173
HMM. [ SCOFFS ]

16:40.173 --> 16:41.808
YOU'RE LYING TO ME.

16:41.808 --> 16:44.244
WHAT?

16:44.244 --> 16:46.847
YEAH. I MEAN...

16:46.847 --> 16:50.083
IF YOU'RE GONNA HELP ME,
I'VE GOT TO TRUST YOU, RIGHT?

16:50.083 --> 16:52.586
YEAH.
YEAH.

16:52.586 --> 16:54.420
YEAH, SO DON'T LIE TO ME.

16:54.420 --> 16:56.189
I'M SORRY.

16:56.189 --> 16:57.924
EVERYBODY HAS DONE IT
MY ENTIRE LIFE.

16:57.924 --> 17:01.001
♪♪♪♪

17:07.407 --> 17:09.309
IS IT A BOYFRIEND?
NO.

17:09.309 --> 17:11.945
[ Chuckling ] NO.

17:11.945 --> 17:13.914
WHO IS IT?

17:13.914 --> 17:15.516
THAT'S PERSONAL.

17:17.784 --> 17:21.421
[ Chuckling ] OH.

17:21.421 --> 17:22.889
I GOT IT. IT'S DR. JARVIS.

17:22.889 --> 17:24.490
HE'S DOING A LITTLE BIT MORE
THAN BEING YOUR BOSS NOW.

17:24.490 --> 17:26.226
OH, MY GOD. NO.

17:26.226 --> 17:27.260
NO! [ CHUCKLES ]

17:27.260 --> 17:29.863
OKAY.

17:29.863 --> 17:31.464
YEAH. YEAH.

17:31.464 --> 17:33.233
THAT WAS HIM ON THE PHONE.
HE'S YOUR PIMP, HUH?

17:33.233 --> 17:35.869
OH, MY GOD.
YEAH.

17:35.869 --> 17:38.238
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU COULD TRY ALL YOU WANT.

17:38.238 --> 17:39.740
I'M NOT GONNA TELL YOU.

17:39.740 --> 17:41.274
WHY NOT?

17:41.274 --> 17:45.078
BECAUSE THE GUY ON THE PHONE,
HE'S JUST NOT WORTH MENTIONING.

17:45.078 --> 17:48.649
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU JUST LET ME
BE THE JUDGE OF THAT?

17:48.649 --> 17:50.116
I WILL NOT.

17:50.116 --> 17:51.284
SO, NOW, TELL ME,
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

17:51.284 --> 17:54.287
YOU WANT SLEEP?
WATCH A MOVIE?

17:54.287 --> 17:56.389
NO. I CAN'T SLEEP.

17:56.389 --> 17:58.625
HERE.

17:58.625 --> 18:00.834
CHOOSE SOMETHING.
YOU'RE GIVING IT TO ME?

18:00.834 --> 18:02.068
YEAH. GO AHEAD.

18:02.068 --> 18:03.937
GOOD.

18:03.937 --> 18:06.172
VERY GOOD. OKAY.

18:06.172 --> 18:08.408
W‐‐ WAIT.

18:08.408 --> 18:10.043
I FEEL A CHICK FLICK
COMING ON.

18:10.043 --> 18:12.078
YES. YOU DO.
GIVE IT BACK TO ME.

18:12.078 --> 18:13.547
NO, YOU CAN'T HAVE IT BACK.

18:13.547 --> 18:14.648
COME ON.

18:14.648 --> 18:16.850
I WILL NOT GIVE IT
BACK TO YOU.

18:19.753 --> 18:21.321
[ CHUCKLES ]
OKAY, FINE. HERE.

18:21.321 --> 18:23.189
YOU CAN HAVE IT.
THANKS.

18:27.427 --> 18:30.631
♪♪♪♪

18:32.999 --> 18:33.934
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:33.934 --> 18:35.969
WHO WERE
YOU TALKING TO?

18:35.969 --> 18:37.971
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE ASLEEP.

18:37.971 --> 18:41.808
YES. I WAS,
BUT I HEARD YOU TALKING.

18:41.808 --> 18:44.678
ROOM SERVICE.
MM.

18:44.678 --> 18:46.446
I GOT YOU SOMETHING TO EAT.

18:46.446 --> 18:47.681
ARE YOU HUNGRY?

18:47.681 --> 18:50.050
NO.

18:50.050 --> 18:52.118
ARE YOU SURE YOU DIDN'T
WORK UP AN APPETITE?

18:52.118 --> 18:54.220
OH, I HAVE AN APPETITE.

18:54.220 --> 18:56.356
YEAH?

18:56.356 --> 18:59.593
WELL, I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND THAT
I'M WEARING YOUR SHIRT.

18:59.593 --> 19:01.267
NOT AT ALL.

19:01.267 --> 19:05.405
IT SMELLS LIKE YOU.

19:05.405 --> 19:07.508
IT LOOKS SEXY AS HELL
ON YOU.

19:07.508 --> 19:09.042
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:09.042 --> 19:10.143
YEAH?

19:10.143 --> 19:11.477
NOTHING SEXIER.

19:13.279 --> 19:14.981
WELL, HOW'S THAT?

19:14.981 --> 19:18.051
OH, SEXIER.

19:18.051 --> 19:19.753
HMM.

19:19.753 --> 19:23.389
I THINK SO, TOO.

19:23.389 --> 19:24.891
THANK YOU.

19:24.891 --> 19:26.593
FOR...?

19:26.593 --> 19:28.962
FOR DEALING
WITH MY SITUATION.

19:28.962 --> 19:31.331
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

19:31.331 --> 19:33.934
WELL, YOU SAID
YOU DON'T DO CRAZY EXES.

19:33.934 --> 19:36.136
OH, NO, YEAH.
YOU'RE RIGHT. I DON'T.

19:36.136 --> 19:38.905
BUT YOURS IS FUN.

19:41.575 --> 19:42.709
ERICA...

19:42.709 --> 19:44.310
NO, SHE'S FUN.

19:44.310 --> 19:45.979
SHE'S...

19:45.979 --> 19:48.014
SHE'S EXTRA.

19:48.014 --> 19:51.251
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

19:51.251 --> 19:54.054
JUST THESE AIRS THAT
SHE PUTS ON,

19:54.054 --> 19:56.256
AND SHE'S SO DRAMATIC.

19:56.256 --> 19:58.458
YES, SHE IS MY...

20:00.260 --> 20:04.237
...EXTRA
VERY‐SOON‐TO‐BE EX.

20:04.237 --> 20:05.672
NOT SOON ENOUGH.

20:05.672 --> 20:07.340
MM, TELL ME ABOUT IT.

20:07.340 --> 20:08.542
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:08.542 --> 20:10.811
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

20:10.811 --> 20:12.846
THAT'S THE PHONE RINGS.

20:16.216 --> 20:17.417
IT'S PROBABLY HER.

20:17.417 --> 20:19.753
YEAH.

20:19.753 --> 20:21.087
NO. IT'S NOT.

20:21.087 --> 20:22.823
HMM?

20:22.823 --> 20:24.691
YES?

20:24.691 --> 20:26.026
DAVID.

20:26.026 --> 20:27.027
YES?

20:27.027 --> 20:29.395
It's Jim.
Where are you?

20:29.395 --> 20:32.098
AT THE ARTESIAN.
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

20:32.098 --> 20:34.267
WE HAVE A PROBLEM, DAVID.

20:34.267 --> 20:36.036
WHAT IS IT NOW?

20:36.036 --> 20:38.371
What room are you in?
I'll come up to you.

20:38.371 --> 20:40.106
NO. NO.

20:40.106 --> 20:41.675
I'LL MEET YOU
IN THE LOBBY.

20:41.675 --> 20:42.943
I'M HERE NOW.

20:42.943 --> 20:44.878
I'M ON MY WAY DOWN.

20:44.878 --> 20:47.213
Good.

20:47.213 --> 20:48.949
[ BEEP ]

20:48.949 --> 20:50.216
MM.

20:50.216 --> 20:51.718
SO, YOU'RE LEAVING?

20:51.718 --> 20:53.554
IT'S BUSINESS.

20:53.554 --> 20:55.355
OH, OKAY.
I'M SORRY.

20:55.355 --> 20:57.323
YEAH, NO PROBLEM.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

20:59.926 --> 21:01.401
YES. YOU WILL.

21:01.401 --> 21:05.205
OKAY.

21:05.205 --> 21:06.940
WELL, I'M TEMPTED
TO STAY DRESSED LIKE THIS

21:06.940 --> 21:08.742
UNTIL I SEE YOU AGAIN.

21:08.742 --> 21:10.310
HMM.

21:10.310 --> 21:12.378
I COULD WORK WITH THAT.

21:12.378 --> 21:15.381
GIVE ME SOMETHING
TO HURRY BACK TO.

21:15.381 --> 21:17.350
WAIT, AM I NOT ENOUGH?

21:17.350 --> 21:18.652
MORE THAN.

21:26.560 --> 21:28.795
BUT I NEED MY SHIRT.

21:28.795 --> 21:30.531
RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

21:30.531 --> 21:33.600
♪♪♪♪

21:52.418 --> 21:54.487
I'LL SEE YOU IN A BIT.

21:54.487 --> 21:55.622
OKAY.

21:55.622 --> 21:59.926
♪♪♪♪

22:13.046 --> 22:15.916
♪♪♪♪

22:30.196 --> 22:33.133
[ Ringing ]

22:33.133 --> 22:34.200
HI, IS THIS VERONICA?

22:34.200 --> 22:35.301
VERONICA: Who is this?

22:35.301 --> 22:37.303
VERONICA,
THIS IS MITCH MALONE.

22:37.303 --> 22:38.138
Malone?

22:38.138 --> 22:39.540
YEP.

22:39.540 --> 22:41.742
You've got my attention.

22:41.742 --> 22:43.409
I'M A FRIEND
OF BENNY YOUNG'S.

22:43.409 --> 22:44.511
What can I do for you?

22:44.511 --> 22:45.912
HE NEEDS A LAWYER.

22:45.912 --> 22:48.715
What makes you think
he doesn't already have one?

22:48.715 --> 22:50.316
ARE YOU
REPRESENTING HIM?

22:50.316 --> 22:51.985
Why?

22:51.985 --> 22:53.219
WELL, IF YOU ARE,
THAT'S GOOD,

22:53.219 --> 22:55.088
BUT HE NEEDS SOME HELP.

22:55.088 --> 22:57.858
I've seen him once,
and I'm here to see him again.

22:57.858 --> 22:59.492
OKAY, GOOD.

22:59.492 --> 23:00.927
I'm in the parking lot.

23:00.927 --> 23:02.335
OKAY, YOU WANT TO
MEET ME IN THE LOBBY?

23:02.335 --> 23:03.770
‐Okay.
‐OKAY, GOOD.

23:03.770 --> 23:05.338
THANK YOU.
‐Sure, Mr. Malone.

23:05.338 --> 23:06.973
‐ALL RIGHT.
‐[ BEEP ]

23:06.973 --> 23:10.010
♪♪♪♪

23:12.913 --> 23:15.381
Mitch: MS. YOUNG, HEY.

23:15.381 --> 23:16.917
MITCHELL.
YEAH.

23:16.917 --> 23:18.351
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH BENNY?

23:18.351 --> 23:19.786
I HAVE NO IDEA.

23:19.786 --> 23:21.588
'CAUSE THESE PEOPLE
WON'T TELL ME NOTHING.

23:21.588 --> 23:22.756
WELL,
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.

23:22.756 --> 23:24.024
HOPEFULLY, WE'LL FIND
SOMETHING OUT, HUH?

23:24.024 --> 23:26.927
‐HEY.
‐HI.
‐HEY.

23:26.927 --> 23:28.895
DID YOU GET IN TOUCH
WITH THE LAWYER?

23:28.895 --> 23:31.231
I SPOKE TO HER.
SHE JUST DROVE UP.

23:31.231 --> 23:33.767
WHO, BENNY'S LAWYER?
YEAH.

23:33.767 --> 23:36.236
WELL, WHO IS IT?

23:36.236 --> 23:38.138
I DON'T KNOW.

23:38.138 --> 23:40.073
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU DON'T KNOW?

23:40.073 --> 23:43.343
I CALLED MARTY.
HE HASN'T CALLED ME BACK.

23:43.343 --> 23:45.579
WHO IS BENNY'S LAWYER?

23:45.579 --> 23:46.680
I JUST SPOKE TO HER
IN THE...

23:46.680 --> 23:48.248
I AM.

23:51.317 --> 23:53.820
OH, NO,
THE HELL YOU AIN'T.

23:53.820 --> 23:57.090
IS THAT A WAY TO SPEAK
TO YOUR SAVING GRACE, MS. HANNA?

23:57.090 --> 24:00.827
YOU AIN'T NONE
OF MY SAVING GRACE.

24:00.827 --> 24:03.336
WELL, I'VE SEEN HIM,
SO I AM HIS LAWYER.

24:03.336 --> 24:06.139
WELL, WHEN I SEE HIM,
HE'LL BE FIRING YOUR ASS.

24:06.139 --> 24:08.108
OKAY. WELL,
I'LL SEE YOU GUYS LATER.

24:08.108 --> 24:09.375
‐BYE.
‐HANNA.

24:09.375 --> 24:11.812
‐WHAT?
‐SHE'S THE BEST,

24:13.947 --> 24:15.816
AND SOMETIMES,
THE DEVIL YOU KNOW

24:15.816 --> 24:17.183
IS BETTER THAN
THE DEVIL YOU DON'T.

24:17.183 --> 24:19.853
I DON'T WANT NO DEVIL
AROUND ME OR MINE.

24:19.853 --> 24:22.155
WOW. WELL, YOU'RE
STANDING NEAR ONE NOW.

24:23.890 --> 24:26.126
IS THAT A REFERENCE
TO ME, VERONICA?

24:26.126 --> 24:28.128
OF COURSE.

24:28.128 --> 24:30.631
NOW, HAVE YOU MET
MR. MITCHELL MALONE?

24:30.631 --> 24:32.332
MALONE?

24:32.332 --> 24:34.434
YEAH.
THE MALONE?

24:34.434 --> 24:37.437
YEAH.

24:37.437 --> 24:38.872
WELL, NOW.

24:42.342 --> 24:44.377
SO, YOU SAY BENNY?
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH HIM?

24:44.377 --> 24:46.246
SHE AIN'T HIS LAWYER!

24:47.914 --> 24:49.516
OKAY, THEN. I WILL LEAVE.

24:49.516 --> 24:50.684
WELL, BYE!

24:50.684 --> 24:51.852
MS. HANNA, COME ON.

24:51.852 --> 24:53.620
‐WHAT?
‐SHE CAN'T HURT.

24:53.620 --> 24:55.121
YES, THE HELL SHE CAN.

24:55.121 --> 24:56.523
LET HER DO IT.

24:56.523 --> 24:59.926
[ Sternly ]
LET HER DO IT.

24:59.926 --> 25:02.402
YOU KNOW WHAT?
ALL THIS CONVINCING...

25:02.402 --> 25:03.369
I CAN GO HOME.

25:03.369 --> 25:04.671
VERONICA CAN GO TO BED.

25:04.671 --> 25:07.741
I AM TIRED ‐‐
WHERE IS HE?

25:07.741 --> 25:09.409
DOES SHE WANT TO KNOW?
YES.

25:09.409 --> 25:11.512
THEN SHE NEEDS
TO ASK ME NICELY.

25:11.512 --> 25:13.413
I AIN'T ASKING
YOUR BLACK ASS NOTHING.

25:13.413 --> 25:15.081
MM.

25:15.081 --> 25:17.483
YOU'RE SO GHETTO,

25:17.483 --> 25:20.787
BUT I UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU'RE GOING THROUGH.

25:20.787 --> 25:24.625
HE WAS BROUGHT IN
ON ATTEMPTED MURDER CHARGES

25:24.625 --> 25:26.993
BUT THEN THE SECRET SERVICE
GOT INVOLVED AND I...

25:26.993 --> 25:28.562
SEE?

25:28.562 --> 25:29.896
SECRET SERVICE?
I...

25:29.896 --> 25:31.164
HOW DID HE EVEN
GET INVOLVED?

25:31.164 --> 25:32.799
I DON'T KNOW.
YEAH, YOU DO.

25:32.799 --> 25:34.400
WHAT ARE YOU TRYING TO DO?

25:34.400 --> 25:35.268
[ SCOFFS ]

25:35.268 --> 25:36.603
YOU UP TO SOMETHING.

25:36.603 --> 25:38.805
I CAN ASSURE YOU,
SHE CAN'T REACH THAT HIGH.

25:38.805 --> 25:40.674
WELL, MY REACH
IS HIGHER THAN YOURS.

25:40.674 --> 25:42.676
OH, YOU CAN
COUNT ON THAT.

25:42.676 --> 25:44.010
I DO.

25:44.010 --> 25:45.579
♪♪♪♪

25:45.579 --> 25:48.915
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

25:48.915 --> 25:50.483
DAMN, JIM.
I'M NOT TALKING TO HIM.

25:50.483 --> 25:52.118
I WANT TO SEE MY SON.

25:52.118 --> 25:54.087
WELL,
I CAN ARRANGE THAT.

25:56.289 --> 25:58.291
WILL YOU PLEASE?

25:58.291 --> 25:59.793
SHE NEEDS TO ASK ME.

25:59.793 --> 26:01.835
‐MS. HANNA.
‐WHAT?

26:01.835 --> 26:03.937
COME ON.

26:03.937 --> 26:05.038
LOOK, VERONICA ‐‐

26:05.038 --> 26:07.373
AND SHE NEEDS
TO ASK ME NICELY.

26:09.175 --> 26:10.210
VERONICA...

26:10.210 --> 26:12.679
GET ON YOUR KNEES.
GO TO HELL.

26:12.679 --> 26:14.414
[ Southern accent ]
ALL RIGHT, MS. TUBMAN.

26:14.414 --> 26:16.016
I'LL JUST GO ON TO HELL.

26:16.016 --> 26:18.084
‐BYE, BYE.
‐SHE IS NOT GETTING

26:18.084 --> 26:19.820
ON HER KNEES, BITCH.

26:19.820 --> 26:21.487
[ Sternly ]
NOW, GET HER IN THERE.

26:21.487 --> 26:24.691
HMM, "BITCH." YES.

26:24.691 --> 26:28.829
DO I NEED TO TELL
A FEW MORE TRUTHS AROUND HERE?

26:28.829 --> 26:31.364
I HAVE A FEW TRUTHS
OF MY OWN,

26:31.364 --> 26:32.833
REMEMBER?

26:32.833 --> 26:35.902
BANG,
BANG‐BANG‐BANG‐BANG.

26:35.902 --> 26:37.704
‐ALL RIGHT.
‐POW.

26:37.704 --> 26:39.840
‐MS. VERONICA...
‐[ CHUCKLES ]

26:39.840 --> 26:42.408
I CAN TELL YOU THAT
MY FAMILY AND I

26:42.408 --> 26:46.913
WOULD BE MOST APPRECIATIVE
IF YOU COULD HELP US SEE BENNY.

26:46.913 --> 26:48.081
WOW.

26:48.081 --> 26:52.318
NOW, SEE, THAT'S HOW SOMEONE
ASKS FOR A FAVOR.

26:53.654 --> 26:54.655
THANK YOU.

26:54.655 --> 26:56.557
I WILL BE HAPPY
TO DO THAT.

26:56.557 --> 27:00.026
THANK YOU.

27:00.026 --> 27:02.903
I'LL SEE
WHAT I CAN DO.

27:02.903 --> 27:04.204
Y'ALL GO ON
AND SIT DOWN NOW,

27:04.204 --> 27:06.907
MS. HANNA.
ALL RIGHT? OKAY.

27:11.645 --> 27:13.580
SEE?
SHE'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

27:13.580 --> 27:16.116
ALL RIGHT?

27:18.719 --> 27:20.921
[ ENGINE STARTS IN DISTANCE ]

27:24.825 --> 27:26.026
[ DOOR OPENS ]

27:27.661 --> 27:28.862
MR. YOUNG?
YEAH.

27:28.862 --> 27:31.197
I'M AGENT VINCE.
THIS IS AGENT HARRIS.

27:31.197 --> 27:32.833
ALL RIGHT. LOOK.

27:32.833 --> 27:35.669
FELLAS, WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON, HERE?

27:35.669 --> 27:37.604
WE NEED A SAMPLE
OF YOUR DNA.

27:37.604 --> 27:39.540
WHAT?
YEAH.

27:39.540 --> 27:42.042
WE NEED TO EXCLUDE YOU
FROM A TERRORISM INVESTIGATION.

27:42.042 --> 27:45.546
LOOK. I DON'T HAVE NOTHING TO DO
WITH NO DAMN TERRORISTS.

27:45.546 --> 27:48.849
♪♪♪♪

27:54.955 --> 27:56.690
YOU KNOW MITCH MALONE?

27:58.592 --> 28:00.761
WHAT ABOUT HIM?
YOU KNOW HIM?

28:00.761 --> 28:03.269
LOOK, I'VE BEEN HERE
FOR A LONG TIME.

28:03.269 --> 28:06.372
OKAY?
WHAT IS GOING ON?

28:06.372 --> 28:09.610
HIS FAMILY IS BEING INVESTIGATED
FOR ORGANIZED CRIME

28:09.610 --> 28:12.378
WHICH TIES INTO
SYRIAN TERRORIST ORGANIZATIONS.

28:12.378 --> 28:14.280
WHAT?

28:14.280 --> 28:16.650
YEAH.

28:16.650 --> 28:19.419
I DON'T KNOW
NOTHING ABOUT THAT.

28:19.419 --> 28:20.954
WELL, WE NEED
TO EXCLUDE YOU.

28:20.954 --> 28:22.923
EXCLUDE ME FROM WHAT?

28:22.923 --> 28:24.090
LOOK, DO YOU WANT
TO GET OUT OF HERE?

28:24.090 --> 28:25.526
NO, I WANT
TO SIT HERE FOR‐‐

28:25.526 --> 28:28.629
HELL YEAH,
I WANT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

28:28.629 --> 28:30.731
LET'S GET YOUR DNA,
AND WE CAN GET YOU OUT.

28:30.731 --> 28:32.432
OKAY. WELL,
I'M NOT DOING THAT.

28:34.334 --> 28:37.504
I'M SORRY.
YOU THINK THIS IS A CHOICE?

28:37.504 --> 28:38.505
YEAH.

28:38.505 --> 28:40.173
LAST TIME I CHECKED,
THIS IS AMERICA.

28:40.173 --> 28:42.609
YEAH, IT'S A CHOICE.

28:42.609 --> 28:43.944
WELL,
YOU'RE NOT IN AMERICA.

28:43.944 --> 28:46.747
OH, I'M NOT. OKAY.
WHERE AM I AT, TOUGH GUY?

28:46.747 --> 28:50.050
YOU'RE IN THE ARMS
OF HOMELAND SECURITY.

28:50.050 --> 28:51.117
LOOK.

28:51.117 --> 28:53.687
YOU CAN GIVE IT TO US
WILLINGLY...

28:53.687 --> 28:55.922
OR WE CAN TAKE IT
FROM YOU.

28:55.922 --> 28:58.291
[ HUFFS ]

28:58.291 --> 28:59.926
WE ‐‐
FINE.

28:59.926 --> 29:02.402
FINE.

29:02.402 --> 29:04.571
FINE. TAKE MY BLOOD,
AND GET ME OUT OF HERE.

29:07.674 --> 29:09.175
FINE.

29:09.175 --> 29:10.443
♪♪♪♪

29:16.817 --> 29:18.919
♪♪♪♪

29:18.919 --> 29:20.921
‐YOU HAVEN'T SEEN THIS?
‐NO, I HAVE NOT SEEN THAT.

29:20.921 --> 29:22.823
IT'S EVERYWHERE.

29:22.823 --> 29:24.925
[ SIGHS ] DAVID?

29:24.925 --> 29:25.859
YEAH.

29:25.859 --> 29:27.160
SHOW HIM.

29:27.160 --> 29:30.697
♪♪♪♪

29:30.697 --> 29:33.466
<i>D.A. JENNIFER SALLISON'S</i>
<i>BODY WAS FOUND HERE...</i>

29:33.466 --> 29:34.835
WHAT THE HELL?

29:34.835 --> 29:38.505
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU HAD THIS ALL HANDLED, DAVID?

29:38.505 --> 29:40.273
OSCAR, PLEASE.

29:40.273 --> 29:43.577
♪♪♪♪

29:47.447 --> 29:48.582
MAMA ROSA HAS THIS
TAKEN CARE OF.

29:48.582 --> 29:49.583
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT

29:49.583 --> 29:51.885
MAMA ROSA?
MAMA ROSA DID THIS!

29:51.885 --> 29:52.819
WHAT?

29:52.819 --> 29:53.987
SHE'S MAD AS HELL AT ME.

29:53.987 --> 29:55.488
WHY?
YOU KNOW MAMA ROSA.

29:55.488 --> 29:56.690
SHE'S GOT THORNS
LIKE NO OTHER.

29:56.690 --> 29:58.525
JIM, WHAT HAPPENED?

30:00.727 --> 30:02.836
WAR TOOK A POTSHOT
AT HER GRANDSON.

30:02.836 --> 30:04.237
I KNOW THAT.

30:04.237 --> 30:05.706
WELL, I'M SUPPOSED
TO FIND WAR,

30:05.706 --> 30:09.309
AND I CAN'T,
SO SHE'S PISSED.

30:09.309 --> 30:10.711
OSCAR...

30:10.711 --> 30:13.179
OSCAR IS USELESS.

30:13.179 --> 30:15.348
WHY THE HELL
CAN'T YOU FIND HIM?

30:15.348 --> 30:16.382
I HAD HIM ON THE PHONE,

30:16.382 --> 30:20.687
AND THEN JIM SPOOKED HIM,
AND WE LOST HIM.

30:20.687 --> 30:22.122
I SEE. THANK YOU.

30:25.291 --> 30:27.427
THIS IS BAD.

30:27.427 --> 30:29.429
I KNOW.

30:29.429 --> 30:30.864
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH
A LOT OF...

30:30.864 --> 30:32.999
YOU AND ME, DAVID,
BUT THIS IS BAD.

30:32.999 --> 30:35.501
I KNOW,
BECAUSE WHEN ROSE IS UPSET...

30:35.501 --> 30:37.871
EVERYBODY IS UPSET.

30:37.871 --> 30:39.005
OKAY. I'LL TALK TO HER.

30:39.005 --> 30:41.908
NO, WHAT ARE YOU?
[ SCOFFS ] CRAZY?

30:41.908 --> 30:43.409
WHAT? ROSE AND I HAVE
A GOOD RELATIONSHIP.

30:43.409 --> 30:46.179
THAT WOMAN WILL HANG YOU IN
THE FREEZER AT HER RESTAURANT.

30:46.179 --> 30:48.414
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

30:48.414 --> 30:51.518
SOMEONE TOOK A POTSHOT
AT MAMA ROSA'S GRANDSON.

30:51.518 --> 30:52.519
I HEARD YOU.

30:52.519 --> 30:54.454
THEN DO YOU GET
WHAT'S GOING ON?

30:54.454 --> 30:55.822
YES.

30:55.822 --> 30:59.726
SOME BLACK KID TAKES A SHOT
AT MAMA ROSA'S GRANDSON,

30:59.726 --> 31:01.267
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT CAUSE
FOR REAL WAR HERE.

31:01.267 --> 31:02.302
I KNOW THAT.

31:02.302 --> 31:04.671
DO YOU REMEMBER
BLOOD RED TUESDAY?

31:04.671 --> 31:07.908
WHEN A BLACK THUG WENT AFTER
ONE OF MAMA ROSA'S THUGS?

31:07.908 --> 31:11.978
SHE TOOK OUT
AN ENTIRE HOUSING PROJECT,

31:11.978 --> 31:13.179
14 PEOPLE DEAD ‐‐

31:13.179 --> 31:15.516
WOMEN, CHILDREN,
EVERY DAMN THING THAT MOVED ‐‐

31:15.516 --> 31:16.783
DEAD.

31:16.783 --> 31:19.119
JIM, I KNOW THAT.
I WAS ON THE BENCH.

31:19.119 --> 31:20.621
YEAH. SO WAS I.
YES.

31:20.621 --> 31:21.855
WE WERE BOTH ON THE BENCH.

31:21.855 --> 31:24.758
AND WE HELPED MAMA ROSA
GET OUT OF THAT MESS.

31:24.758 --> 31:27.127
THAT'S WHY I NEED
TO GO TALK TO HER.

31:27.127 --> 31:28.161
IT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY DIFFERENCE, DAVID.

31:28.161 --> 31:29.763
THIS IS DIFFERENT.

31:29.763 --> 31:32.666
IT'S US THAT SHE'S MAD AT.

31:32.666 --> 31:36.703
IT'S US THAT GOT WAR
OUT OF JAIL.

31:36.703 --> 31:37.704
DAMN IT

31:41.041 --> 31:42.943
WE NEED TO CONTROL
THE DAMAGE SOMEHOW.

31:42.943 --> 31:45.879
YEAH,
IT'S ALREADY STARTED.

31:45.879 --> 31:48.414
I GOT TO GET KATHERYN
ON THE PHONE.

31:48.414 --> 31:50.350
THEY'RE GONNA TRY TO CALL HER,
BUT SHE WON'T TAKE MY CALLS.

31:50.350 --> 31:51.484
CAN YOU CALL HER FOR ME?

31:51.484 --> 31:52.619
[ SIGHS ]

31:52.619 --> 31:54.287
YES.

31:54.287 --> 31:55.722
THANK YOU.

31:55.722 --> 31:57.558
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU LOOKING AT, HUH?

31:59.660 --> 32:03.069
YOU JUST FIND THAT DAMN KID.
‐[ BEEP ]

32:03.069 --> 32:04.938
This is Katheryn.
Please leave a message.

32:04.938 --> 32:06.239
KATHERYN...

32:06.239 --> 32:07.340
IT'S DAVID.

32:07.340 --> 32:09.275
WHEN YOU GET THIS,
WILL YOU PLEASE CALL ME?

32:09.275 --> 32:10.711
IT'S URGENT.

32:10.711 --> 32:13.714
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"I CAN'T HAVE MY OLD NUMBER"?

32:13.714 --> 32:15.248
[ DOOR OPENS ]

32:15.248 --> 32:18.318
IT'S BEEN GIVEN TO WHO?

32:18.318 --> 32:19.886
WHAT?

32:19.886 --> 32:21.955
NO, I ‐‐
I DIDN'T CANCEL IT.

32:23.890 --> 32:26.292
OKAY. [ SCOFFS ]

32:26.292 --> 32:28.261
OKAY.
OKAY. THANK YOU.

32:28.261 --> 32:31.197
[ BEEP ]

32:31.197 --> 32:33.967
HAVING TROUBLE
GETTING A NEW PHONE?

32:33.967 --> 32:36.603
I JUST WANT
MY OLD NUMBER.

32:36.603 --> 32:38.238
I DON'T THINK
YOU CAN GET THAT.

32:38.238 --> 32:41.241
[ SIGHS ]

32:41.241 --> 32:42.643
CHARLES...

32:44.611 --> 32:45.879
GET A NEW ONE.

32:47.280 --> 32:49.916
THAT'S NOT GOING TO HELP
WITH MY CONTACTS.

32:51.351 --> 32:54.755
YOU DON'T NEED TO KEEP IN TOUCH
WITH THOSE PEOPLE ANYMORE.

32:54.755 --> 32:56.557
YOU KNOW I HAVE
A SON, RIGHT?

32:56.557 --> 32:58.892
YEAH. I DO.

32:58.892 --> 33:01.968
WHAT IF
HE'S TRYING TO CALL ME?

33:01.968 --> 33:04.404
CALL YOUR MOTHER.

33:04.404 --> 33:06.873
SHE HAS CUSTODY.

33:06.873 --> 33:08.842
I DON'T LIKE THIS.

33:08.842 --> 33:10.176
WHAT?

33:10.176 --> 33:12.779
THIS SITUATION.

33:12.779 --> 33:14.715
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:14.715 --> 33:16.650
WHY?

33:16.650 --> 33:18.018
IS IT BECAUSE
I HAVE THE UPPER HAND

33:18.018 --> 33:21.454
SINCE I HAVE
ALL THE INFORMATION?

33:21.454 --> 33:22.956
HOW DO YOU KNOW
ALL THIS?

33:22.956 --> 33:25.458
THIS IS ILLEGAL.

33:25.458 --> 33:27.628
NOT THESE DAYS.

33:27.628 --> 33:28.895
[ SCOFFS ]

33:28.895 --> 33:30.030
REALLY?

33:30.030 --> 33:32.265
NO.

33:32.265 --> 33:34.668
EVERYTHING IS
ACCESSIBLE,

33:34.668 --> 33:36.436
THESE PHONES...

33:36.436 --> 33:39.606
THE COMPUTERS,
EVERYTHING.

33:39.606 --> 33:41.775
WE CAN GET ALL YOU NEED.

33:41.775 --> 33:42.743
I SEE THAT.

33:42.743 --> 33:45.679
YOU SHOULD
BE MORE CAREFUL.

33:45.679 --> 33:48.882
I DON'T LIKE BEING TREATED
LIKE A PRISONER.

33:48.882 --> 33:50.751
WHO'S DOING THAT?

33:50.751 --> 33:52.919
YOU ARE
BY WITHHOLDING MY PHONES.

33:52.919 --> 33:54.888
I'M NOT HOLDING THEM.

33:54.888 --> 33:56.857
WELL, THEN,
GIVE THEM BACK.

33:56.857 --> 33:58.124
THEY'VE BEEN DESTROYED.

34:00.226 --> 34:01.735
OKAY.

34:01.735 --> 34:03.604
GREAT.

34:03.604 --> 34:06.372
COME ON.

34:06.372 --> 34:08.909
A NEW START
ISN'T SUCH A BAD THING.

34:08.909 --> 34:11.545
I DON'T WANT A NEW START.

34:11.545 --> 34:13.346
YOU KNOW WHAT
I'M OFFERING YOU HERE?

34:13.346 --> 34:15.682
DO I GET A CHOICE
IN THE OFFER?

34:15.682 --> 34:17.250
HOW MANY TIMES
ARE YOU GONNA GET THE CHANCE

34:17.250 --> 34:20.153
TO WIPE YOUR PAST CLEAN?

34:20.153 --> 34:21.454
PEOPLE HAVE MEMORIES.

34:21.454 --> 34:23.790
NOT OF THINGS
THEY DON'T WANT TO GET OUT.

34:25.559 --> 34:26.960
YEAH.

34:26.960 --> 34:27.928
YOU'RE...

34:27.928 --> 34:29.295
YOU'RE RIGHT.

34:29.295 --> 34:31.431
YES. I AM.

34:32.933 --> 34:35.969
[ SIGHS ]

34:35.969 --> 34:37.971
SO WHAT'S THE PLAN?

34:37.971 --> 34:39.305
PLAN?

34:39.305 --> 34:41.775
YEAH, YOU'RE ‐‐
YOU'RE DOING ALL THESE THINGS.

34:41.775 --> 34:44.611
Y‐YOU HAVE A PLAN.

34:44.611 --> 34:46.513
NO PLAN.

34:46.513 --> 34:48.949
CHARLES?

34:48.949 --> 34:50.784
I JUST WANT
TO GIVE YOU A NEW START.

34:53.286 --> 34:57.591
AND WHY WOULD YOU WANT
TO DO THAT?

34:57.591 --> 34:59.960
SO YOU CAN BE AROUND ME
WHEN I'M PRESIDENT.

35:02.235 --> 35:03.504
CHARLES...

35:03.504 --> 35:06.707
LOOK.

35:06.707 --> 35:08.609
I TOLD YOU,

35:08.609 --> 35:12.345
THAT BUBBLE IS SMALL.

35:12.345 --> 35:14.080
SO I'M GETTING PREPARED
TO ENTER IT

35:14.080 --> 35:15.281
WITH A HEALTHY LIST OF...

35:15.281 --> 35:18.184
I DON'T WANT
TO BE ON A LIST.

35:18.184 --> 35:20.353
SURE YOU WILL.

35:20.353 --> 35:23.089
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU'RE SO CONCEITED.

35:23.089 --> 35:25.091
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:25.091 --> 35:27.193
ONLY IN PRIVATE.

35:27.193 --> 35:29.996
THIS IS CRAZY.

35:29.996 --> 35:33.199
YOU DON'T WANT A DO‐OVER?

35:33.199 --> 35:35.035
BE RESPECTED...

35:35.035 --> 35:37.638
AND RESPECTABLE?

35:37.638 --> 35:38.905
IT CAN'T BE DONE.

35:38.905 --> 35:41.374
YES, IT CAN.

35:41.374 --> 35:43.309
LOOK AT ME.

35:43.309 --> 35:46.079
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

35:46.079 --> 35:48.248
LETS JUST SAY...

35:48.248 --> 35:51.585
I WAS PLUCKED
FROM THE MILITARY,

35:51.585 --> 35:54.020
SENT TO COLLEGE

35:54.020 --> 35:56.623
AND PUT IN THE SENATE,

35:56.623 --> 35:59.660
GROOMED FOR THIS DAY.

35:59.660 --> 36:01.234
ALL MY PAST WENT AWAY.

36:03.937 --> 36:05.772
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

36:05.772 --> 36:06.707
YEAH.

36:09.743 --> 36:11.077
THIS IS UNREAL.

36:11.077 --> 36:14.280
[ CHUCKLES ]
THIS IS POLITICS.

36:15.516 --> 36:18.418
NOW, TAKE THIS RESET
AND ENJOY IT.

36:20.621 --> 36:23.724
AND YOU GET TO BE ONE
OF THE PRESIDENT'S REGULARS.

36:23.724 --> 36:25.859
A REGULAR WHAT?

36:28.061 --> 36:29.596
WOMEN.

36:29.596 --> 36:30.797
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:30.797 --> 36:32.666
EXCUSE ME?

36:32.666 --> 36:35.769
I'M GONNA CLEAN YOU UP,

36:35.769 --> 36:37.504
MAKE YOU ABLE TO PASS.

36:39.806 --> 36:43.376
NOW, I'VE ACTUALLY BEEN
LOOKING FOR SOMEONE LIKE YOU,

36:43.376 --> 36:46.947
SOMEONE WITH
JUST ENOUGH CLASS,

36:46.947 --> 36:48.949
THE RIGHT LOOK...

36:48.949 --> 36:50.717
AND JUST ENOUGH DIRT.

36:53.086 --> 36:56.089
[ SCOFFS ]
SO, I'M A PROJECT NOW?

36:57.524 --> 36:58.892
YEAH.

36:58.892 --> 37:01.167
AH.

37:01.167 --> 37:02.468
WELL, THAT MAKES ME
FEEL LIKE CRAP.

37:02.468 --> 37:05.038
DON'T.

37:05.038 --> 37:06.840
I REALLY LIKE YOU.

37:06.840 --> 37:09.943
CHARLES...

37:09.943 --> 37:10.710
CHARLES ‐‐

37:10.710 --> 37:12.646
CANDACE, LOOK AT ME.

37:14.581 --> 37:16.683
YOU DON'T WANT
A CLEAN SLATE?

37:22.122 --> 37:24.691
GO TO SCHOOL.

37:24.691 --> 37:27.360
FINALLY GET YOUR DEGREE.

37:27.360 --> 37:29.630
WE CAN MAKE THAT HAPPEN.

37:29.630 --> 37:31.431
GET YOU A HOUSE,

37:31.431 --> 37:33.800
PUT YOU UP,

37:33.800 --> 37:36.236
MAKE YOU STRONG,

37:36.236 --> 37:38.505
INDEPENDENT,

37:38.505 --> 37:42.242
SELF‐SUFFICIENT.

37:42.242 --> 37:43.376
YOU'LL HAVE POWER.

37:47.814 --> 37:49.082
BUT WHY?

37:49.082 --> 37:51.451
I WANT YOU.

37:51.451 --> 37:54.087
THAT'S WHY.

37:54.087 --> 37:55.789
AND THAT'S ALL?

37:55.789 --> 37:58.158
YES.

37:58.158 --> 38:00.160
AREN'T YOU TIRED?
[ SIGHS ]

38:00.160 --> 38:01.535
AREN'T YOU?

38:04.638 --> 38:07.874
‐YES.
‐WOULDN'T IT BE GREAT TO REST

38:07.874 --> 38:10.043
AND NOT HAVE TO LOOK
OVER YOUR SHOULDER,

38:10.043 --> 38:11.778
HONESTLY?

38:13.847 --> 38:15.549
YES.

38:15.549 --> 38:19.786
THEN, TAKE THIS CHANCE.

38:19.786 --> 38:21.387
NOBODY GETS IT.

38:24.390 --> 38:25.992
YOU DID.

38:25.992 --> 38:28.629
YEAH. I DID.

38:30.096 --> 38:32.999
IF I SAID "YES"...

38:32.999 --> 38:34.234
YOU WOULD OWN ME.

38:34.234 --> 38:37.671
[ SCOFFS ]

38:37.671 --> 38:39.439
NO.

38:39.439 --> 38:40.907
I WOULDN'T.

38:40.907 --> 38:42.242
SOMEONE WOULD.

38:42.242 --> 38:43.544
NO.

38:43.544 --> 38:45.378
THAT'S NOT
HOW THIS WORKS.

38:47.280 --> 38:50.717
YOU JUST STAY STRAIGHT,
AND YOU LIVE FINE.

38:52.185 --> 38:54.120
YOU TAKE CARE OF ME,

38:54.120 --> 38:57.390
AND I'LL TAKE CARE OF YOU.

38:57.390 --> 38:58.992
NOW, THEY'VE FOUND
SOME WOMEN FOR ME

38:58.992 --> 39:02.669
BUT NONE OF THEM HAVE BEEN
AS AMAZING AS YOU ARE.

39:02.669 --> 39:06.006
♪♪♪♪

39:06.006 --> 39:09.510
WHEN YOU SAY "THEY,"
WHO ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

39:09.510 --> 39:11.244
YOU DON'T GET IT.

39:11.244 --> 39:14.380
THESE SUPER PACs ARE
SOME VERY POWERFUL PEOPLE.

39:16.216 --> 39:17.784
SAY "YES."

39:20.687 --> 39:22.989
I WILL NOT BE A NUMBER.

39:22.989 --> 39:24.625
OKAY.

39:24.625 --> 39:26.126
THEN BE THE ONLY ONE.

39:27.928 --> 39:29.229
[ SIGHS ]

39:32.733 --> 39:34.535
MAKE ME YOUR FIRST LADY.

39:34.535 --> 39:35.736
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:38.371 --> 39:39.806
DON'T TELL ME
YOUR ONE OF THOSE,

39:39.806 --> 39:42.743
LIKE, YOU GIVE THEM AN INCH,
AND THEY WANT A MILE.

39:44.410 --> 39:47.480
YOU SAID
YOU CAN DO ANYTHING,

39:47.480 --> 39:49.382
AND IT'S BUSINESS,
RIGHT?

39:53.086 --> 39:54.588
THAT'S NOT
GOING TO HAPPEN.

39:57.591 --> 40:00.594
AND IF I SAY "NO"?

40:00.594 --> 40:03.637
THEN, YOU GO BACK
TO YOUR OLD LIFE.

40:03.637 --> 40:06.072
ARE THERE GOOD THINGS
WAITING FOR YOU THERE?

40:07.808 --> 40:10.577
NO.
NO. I DIDN'T THINK SO.

40:10.577 --> 40:15.415
SO, THIS SEEMS
LIKE A NO‐BRAINER TO ME.

40:15.415 --> 40:16.983
ALTHOUGH...

40:16.983 --> 40:19.853
THERE IS ONE MATTER.

40:19.853 --> 40:21.487
HMM. YEP.

40:21.487 --> 40:22.723
I KNEW THERE WAS A CATCH.

40:22.723 --> 40:24.324
THERE WAS A MURDER...

40:24.324 --> 40:25.626
AND A BODY.

40:28.629 --> 40:30.330
YOU CAN MAKE THAT
GO AWAY?

40:32.332 --> 40:34.000
[ SIGHS ]

40:34.000 --> 40:36.670
TOO PUBLIC.

40:36.670 --> 40:38.639
SOMEONE HAS TO TAKE
THE FALL FOR IT.

40:40.841 --> 40:42.208
YOU CAN
MAKE THAT HAPPEN?

40:42.208 --> 40:44.110
YEAH.

40:44.110 --> 40:45.646
IT'S BEING DONE NOW.

40:48.381 --> 40:51.852
WHO?

40:51.852 --> 40:54.621
YOUR BROTHER.

40:54.621 --> 40:56.523
W‐WHAT?

40:56.523 --> 41:00.293
YEAH. HE'S IN CUSTODY NOW.
NOW, YOU HAVE TO UNDERSTAND,

41:00.293 --> 41:02.569
THERE ARE CASUALTIES
TO LIVE THIS LIFE.

41:02.569 --> 41:06.439
WAIT? MY BROTHER?

41:06.439 --> 41:08.374
ALL YOU GOT TO DO
IS SAY "YES."

41:08.374 --> 41:12.145
AND GIVE UP MY BROTHER?

41:12.145 --> 41:13.947
WHAT'S YOUR CHOICE?

41:13.947 --> 41:16.349
♪♪♪♪

41:16.349 --> 41:17.851
[ SCOFFS ]

41:27.561 --> 41:29.963
<i>NEXT ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:29.963 --> 41:31.998
SHE DONE LOST
YOUR TOW YARD,

41:31.998 --> 41:34.601
YOUR HOUSE,
YOUR TRUCK, MY HOUSE.

41:34.601 --> 41:37.103
SHE IS NOTHING,
BUT A WALKING TSUNAMI.

41:37.103 --> 41:38.505
SHE JUST SLAPPED ME!

41:38.505 --> 41:39.806
LOOK, I'MA GET HER,
ALL RIGHT?

41:39.806 --> 41:42.308
OH, MY GOD! I‐I ‐‐
I HATE THAT HO!

41:42.308 --> 41:44.578
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT I'M CAPABLE OF.

41:44.578 --> 41:45.912
NO.

41:45.912 --> 41:49.315
YOUR WIFE HAS NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE CAPABLE OF.

41:49.315 --> 41:50.851
YOU KNOW,
I'M GONNA BE SINGLE SOON.

41:54.855 --> 41:56.590
I COULD USE A MAN
LIKE YOU.
